<br>
That's one reason I opt for an illusion vs. a shrink.  Being able to see.  I usually try to play to one side of the direction of the pull.  Assist the puller, change target and start rooting / mezzing.  If you get aggro - stand still so the melees don't have to chase you.<br>
<br>
If you're playing a new zone and fighting mobs you don't know, always test to see if they can be mezzed, slowed, rooted, etc.  Hopefully, you can do this when a mob is at 20% HPs.<br>
<br>
